A1010/26 and replacement A1015/26.","source_url":"https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269 and https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/67435351-52f9-4d17-8f4c-497a21dd94bf","storage_name":"5e/5e5109b5ca632110b53c1e6f333fa92259a70d8b970b57de188d7b8dbcc1bce7","submitted_by_role":"defendant","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"Notamify raw text for OIIX A1010/26 and replacement A1015/26"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T14:27:42Z","evidence_id":"ev_6057a17cc5bf_submitted-evidence-04-defendant-6057a17cc5bf","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-04-defendant-6057a17cc5bf.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Provides a contrary/source-chain complication: Iran's Civil Aviation Organization spokesperson reportedly denied a new official aviation notice imposing nationwide airspace restrictions and said flights were operating according to schedule, while the same report acknowledges an earlier western-Tehran-FIR airport activity suspension with exemptions.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T14:28:45Z","sha256":"6057a17cc5bf9d03bc6a13a3f87c381c3974e116d8d6e2a3a9ecd39961ab6e61","size_bytes":1142,"source_description":"Iran International webpage retrieved via web open on 2026-06-30; captured article title, timestamp, and relevant lines 39-55.","source_url":"https://www.iranintl.com/en/202605239595","storage_name":"60/6057a17cc5bf9d03bc6a13a3f87c381c3974e116d8d6e2a3a9ecd39961ab6e61","submitted_by_role":"defendant","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"Iran International report: Iran denies new NOTAM limiting flights across country"},{"admissibility_status":"submitted_evidence","created_at":"2026-06-30T14:24:42Z","evidence_id":"ev_6877e32e36e2_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-6877e32e36e2","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-6877e32e36e2.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","relevance":"Reports that Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM OIIX A1010/26 on May 22, valid until May 25, closing all airports in the western Tehran FIR and limiting remaining airports to daylight operations with fresh per-flight CAA approval.","retrieval_timestamp":"2026-06-30T14:25:00Z","sha256":"6877e32e36e2b58bf10a9b2d917614c815931dc94d707627c69bb1fc195f509c","size_bytes":1524,"source_description":"The Indian Express webpage captured via web open; selected relevant page text and metadata from lines 20-61 and 100-115.","source_url":"https://indianexpress.com/article/world/us-news/iran-closes-airspace-trump-cancels-plans-us-military-strikes-rubio-india-10704692/","storage_name":"68/6877e32e36e2b58bf10a9b2d917614c815931dc94d707627c69bb1fc195f509c","submitted_by_role":"plaintiff","submitted_phase":"arguments","text_readable":true,"title":"Indian Express report on Iran western airspace closure, May 23 2026"},{"admissibility_status":"case_packet","created_at":"2026-06-30T14:16:53Z","evidence_id":"ev_e61df84283cc_market-page","mime_type":"text/plain","original_name":"market-page.txt","record_visibility":"juror_visible","sha256":"e61df84283cc858bfd0cf8235c6f1d53a10d6e1c37b2d97256da8f1e6391cc17","size_bytes":4971,"source_description":"Initial case packet file","storage_name":"e6/e61df84283cc858bfd0cf8235c6f1d53a10d6e1c37b2d97256da8f1e6391cc17","submitted_by_role":"system","submitted_phase":"case_packet","text_readable":true,"title":"market-page.txt"}]},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-30T14:49:55.325794347Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C2","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C2","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":882215,"role_id":"council","turn_number":10}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"list_evidence"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782830113111},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the evidence and arguments presented, I will now cast my vote. Let me analyze the key elements:\n\n1. The market rule requires Iran to initiate a \"major closure\" that is not solely weather-related by May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET.\n2. A \"major closure\" is defined as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region.\n3. The evidence shows that NOTAM OIIX A1010/26, issued by Iran's Civil Aviation Authority on May 22, closed all airports in the west part of the Tehran FIR (a major Iranian airspace region), allowing only specific airports to operate during daylight hours with fresh CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights.\n4. The restriction was in effect until May 25, past the May 24 deadline.\n5. The restriction was non-weather related, due to security and military/diplomatic tensions.\n\nFrom the defendant's own evidence (DX-1), we can see the raw NOTAM text explicitly states: \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD EXCEPT...\" followed by a small number of specific airports that could operate only during daylight hours with new permissions required. This represents a broad closure with limited exceptions, which is explicitly allowed under the market rule.\n\nThe evidence shows that Iran initiated this closure, it covered a major Iranian airspace region (the western part of the Tehran FIR), and it was in effect before the May 24 deadline. Despite the defendant's arguments, the listed exceptions (sunrise to sunset operations with fresh CAA approval) represent limited exceptions to an otherwise broad closure, as contemplated by the rule.\n\nI'll submit my vote now:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1e4371e364b2453f89d83638","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran initiated a broad closure of western Tehran FIR effective May 22 until May 25, 2026, with limited exceptions only for daylight operations requiring fresh CAA approval. This constitutes a major non-weather closure of a major Iranian airspace region within the market rule's definition by the May 24 deadline.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":40447,"output":491,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40938,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782830113112,"responseId":"gen-1782830113-xBU0jApvNtQDid6NmP6L"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1e4371e364b2453f89d83638","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C2\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260630141638\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C2\nremaining_ms: 870049\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260630141638\",\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T14:49:55.325794347Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C2\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":870049,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":10}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C2\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260630141638\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C2\nremaining_ms: 870049\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260630141638\",\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T14:49:55.325794347Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C2\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C2\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":870049,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":10}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex11a-20260630141638","member_id":"C2","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-30T14:49:55.325794347Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C2","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C2","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":870049,"role_id":"council","turn_number":10}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782830125279},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My vote has been accepted. As council member C2, I voted that the proposition was demonstrated, with the rationale that the admitted evidence shows Iran initiated a broad closure of western Tehran FIR effective May 22 until May 25, 2026, with limited exceptions only for daylight operations requiring fresh CAA approval. This constituted a major non-weather closure of a major Iranian airspace region within the market rule's definition by the May 24 deadline."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-plus","usage":{"input":786,"output":95,"cacheRead":40384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41265,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782830125283,"responseId":"gen-1782830125-izs1flKZkCCuwy6kTyzl"}],"willRetry":false}
